Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
run_vsr(25.10)                                                  run_vsr(25.10)

Name
       run_vsr - Launches the Virtuoso Space-based Router (VSR) from Innovustm
       Implementation System

Syntax
       run_vsr

        [-help]

        [-log_file <fileName>]

        [-no_taper_to_pinwidth]

        [-post_load_script <scriptname>]

        [-pre_load_script <scriptname>]

        [-remove_existing_route]

        [-route_type_order {bus diffPair match nets shield}]

       [-run_VSR_Script <scriptname>]

        [-share_shields]

        [-sel_net <list_of_selected_nets> | -incl_net_type {bus diffPair match
       nets shield} | -nets_file <fileName>]

       Launches the Virtuoso Space-based Router (VSR) from Innovustm Implemen-
       tation  System.  It works on OpenAccess design as well as restored non-
       OpenAccess designs. It routes the nets  specified  with  the  -sel_net,
       -nets_file,  or  -incl_net_type option. If the -incl_net_type option is
       used, the nets are routed in the following order: diffPair, match, bus,
       nets, and shield. To invoke this wrapper, make sure Virtuoso is  avail-
       able in your path.

       Before running the run_vsr command, set the following:

       setOaxMode -compressLevel 1

       Notes

              * Integration  constraints  are used to convey the design intent
                in a mixed-signal design. These constraints are fully interop-
                erable between the digital and custom environments.

              *

                If you run run_vsr on an abstract inferred  from  layout,  you
                may see the following WARNING message:

                "The current database uses quick abstract inference and should
                be used only for floorplanning and not for routing purposes."

       For  more  information on using run_vsr, see the Routing Constraint In-
       teroperability chapter in the Mixed Signal Interoperability Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each run_vsr parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

               man run_vsr

       -incl_net_type {bus diffPair match nets shield}
              Specifies the list of valid net types for VSR to route.

              Note:  The  -sel_net,  -nets_file, and -incl_net_type parameters
              are mutually exclusive. Do not specify these parameters  at  the
              same time.

       -log_file <fileName>
              Specifies the file name for writing the routing report.

       -nets_file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file listing the nets to be routed.

              Note:  The  -sel_net,  -nets_file, and -incl_net_type parameters
              are mutually exclusive. Do not specify these parameters  at  the
              same time.

       -no_taper_to_pinwidth
              Does  not perform tapering based on the pin width. For instance,
              if the rule applied on a mixed signal net is  NDR1  whose  width
              exceeds the pin width for a particular layer, then VSR automati-
              cally  tapers the wire to match the pin width. If this option is
              specified, then tapering is not done.

       -post_load_script <scriptname>
              Specifies the name of the script to be  executed  by  VSR  after
              loading the design.

       -pre_load_script <scriptname>
              Specifies  the  name  of the script to be executed by VSR before
              loading the design.

       -remove_existing_route
              Deletes the nets (fixed, normal), including shield, and  exclud-
              ing  power  nets,  which are specified by the -sel_net parameter
              before routing

       -route_type_order {bus diffPair match nets shield}
              Specifies the list of valid constraint types  in  the  preferred
              routing order.

       -run_VSR_Script <scriptname>
              Specifies  a  user-defined  script  to  be run by VSR for custom
              routing. If this option is specified, the router skips all  pre-
              setting  from VSR and routes the design by sourcing the complete
              custom script as provided.

       -share_shields
              Shares the shielded nets. Using this parameter, you  can  selec-
              tively specify the list of shared shielded nets.

       -sel_net <list_of_selected_nets>
              Specifies the list of nets that have to be routed.

Using Scripts and Environmental Variables with run_vsr
       The  run_vsr  command  in  Innovus supports a limited set of options to
       route the analog/mixed-signal nets. To have more control of the VSR en-
       gine, you can set additional settings through the .cdsenv file.

       Settings through .cdsenv

       Here are two examples of how you can use .cdsenv  settings  to  control
       VSR:

              * To force VSR to route on-grid:

                layout routeUseGrid cyclic "Routing"

              * To force VSR to use the rules from the specified route spec:

                layout wireConstraintGroup string "LEFDefaultRouteSpec"

       If  you  set  the above settings in the .cdsenv file before running the
       run_vsr command, Virtuoso initializes them before calling the  VSR  en-
       gine.

       In  addition  to the settings through .cdsenv file, the run_vsr command
       is  enhanced  to  pass  additional   variables   or   scripts   through
       -pre_load_script and -post_load_script.

       Preloadscript

       Usage of settings through -pre_load_script is only for expert VSR users
       and generally not recommended.

       Postloadscript

       Example:

              * To  enable VSR to use the custom vias and not generated or de-
                rived vias:

                setvar db.enable_create_derived_vias false

              * To enable VSR to connect the wires to the center of the pin

                setvar droute.snap_to_pin_center true

       You can set the above environmental variables in a  script  and  enable
       them through the following command:

       run_vsr -sel_net { neta .....} -post_load_script scriptname...

       For  more  information on the environmental variables which can be set,
       refer to the following documentation:

              * "Environment Variables" chapter  in  the  Cadence  Space-based
                Router and Chip Optimizer Command Reference

       Note: Consult Cadence for the best use of these variables to obtain the
       desired results.

Examples
              * The following command routes the bus nets using VSR:

                run_vsr  -sel_net  {DATA[0]  DATA[1]  DATA[2]  DATA[3] DATA[4]
                DATA[5] DATA[6] DATA[7]}

              * The following command routes the given  net  lbk_bstart  using
                mixed-signal constraint, if any constraint has been applied to
                this net which will be taken from OpenAccess database:

                run_vsr -sel_net lbk_bstart

              * The following command routes all the nets which have diffPair,
                matchPair  and  then  net class in the following order of con-
                straint types:

                run_vsr -incl_net_type {diffPair match nets}

Related Information
